         <div type="commentary">
            <p>We have no other Eupeithios so far attested at Aphrodisias in the Roman period, but one (? a sophist) honoured in ? the fourth/fifth century ( <ref type="inscription" n="33" target="iAph050120"/>).</p>
            <p>It is standard for the pious to be thought of as inhabiting a special and honoured place; here the idea is carried farther, presenting Eupeithios as god-like.</p>
         </div>
